Step 1: 

To download a file from GitHub, start by clicking the Go to file button at the top of the repo contents.

This will pull up a page that lists all of the files in the GitHub repository. 

Step 2:

Click on the file you wish to download from GitHub to open the individual file. From here, right click the Raw button at the top of the file, select Save Link Asâ€¦, choose the location on your computer where you want to save the file, and select Save
